        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best review management tool for small businesses?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">NiceJob ($75/month) best fits small businesses due to its automation simplicity and minimal setup. BrightLocal ($39-59/month) covers the basics if monitoring only is needed. Google Business Profile (free) is the baseline every business needs before any paid tool.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many reviews does a business need to rank well on Google?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Fifty or more Google reviews with a 4.0+ average rating consistently outrank competitors with fewer reviews. Review velocity matters — 5-10 new reviews monthly signal activity to Google. Consistent generation matters more than one-time volume.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I manage reviews on Google, Yelp, and Facebook from one tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Birdeye covers 200+ sites, ReviewTrackers covers 100+, and BrightLocal covers major platforms including Google, Yelp, and Facebook. Podium focuses on Google and Facebook only.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do review management tools actually increase your star rating?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Indirectly, yes. Tools automating review requests generate more reviews from satisfied customers. Since most satisfied customers rate 4-5 stars, the influx of positive reviews raises your average. Tools don't filter negative reviews — they increase positive volume.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How fast should a business respond to reviews?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Within 24 hours for negative reviews, within 48 hours for positive reviews. Google's local ranking algorithm factors in response rate and speed. Businesses responding to 80%+ of reviews within 24 hours see measurable ranking benefits.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Trustpilot worth it for local businesses?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For most local businesses, no. Trustpilot's strength is ecommerce and B2B where Google rich snippet integration adds star ratings to search results. Local businesses should prioritize Google, Yelp, and Facebook reviews first before investing in Trustpilot.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between review monitoring and review management?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
